headline: Costco’s March Was Strong. Tariff Uncertainty Didn’t Stop Consumers.
summary: March was another strong month for  Costco  Wholesale, suggesting consumer demand for bulk buying wasn’t dampened by macroeconomic uncertainty.  Costco’s March sales increased by 8.6% year over year to $25.5 billion, slightly decelerating from February’s 8.8% increase but still pointing to strong sales trends for the month.  Fresh foods were a top category last month, with sales up by low double digits, said Josh Dahmen, assistant vice president of financial planning and investor relations.

headline: Costco Wholesale Corporation Reports March Sales Results
summary: ISSAQUAH, Wash., April 09, 2025 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- Costco Wholesale Corporation (“Costco” or the “Company”) (Nasdaq: COST) today reported net sales of $25.51 billion for the retail month of March, the five weeks ended April 6, 2025, an increase of 8.6 percent from $23.48 billion last year. Net sales for the first 31 weeks were $158.87 billion, an increase of 8.3 percent from $146.64 billion last year.
